opennlp.ccg.realize
Class Tracker

java.lang.Object
  opennlp.ccg.realize.Tracker
Direct Known Subclasses:
Edge, RuleInstance
public class Tracker
extends Object

A tracker is a wrapper for either a sign (ie, an edge) or a type changing rule (ie, a rule instance) which has bitsets for representing the coverage of the input predicates and the semantic indices used. It also has a list of active LF alts. Trackers are created by an EdgeFactory. The design follows the Singleton pattern.
